<img width="674" height="379" class="wp-image-1799518" style="width: 600px;" src="https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/INEC.jpg" alt="INEC" srcset="https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/INEC.jpg?width=674&amp;auto_optimize=medium 674w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/INEC-300x169.jpg?width=300&amp;auto_optimize=medium 300w" sizes="(max-width: 674px) 100vw, 674px" /> By Rotimi Ojomoyela THE Independent National Electoral Commission, INEC, in Ekiti State, yesterday distributed the sensitive materials meant for tomorrowâ€™s governorship election in the state. The distribution started at the INEC state office in Ado Ekiti in the presence of journalists, party and security agents to the Electoral officers in the 16 local councils. The Resident Electoral Commissioner, Dr Adeniran Tella, who distributed the materials, said the electoral officers would take the items to their councils where it would be sent to the polling units on Saturday morning. He expressed hope that there would be no late arrival of materials to polling units tomorrow. Dr Tella said the ballot papers were colour coded for each local government in order to prevent electoral fraud. He added that the result sheets were also customized according to the polling units. Some of the party agents including Mr Kayode Babade of the APC, Mr Kehinde Adeniyi of the ADC and IPAC Chairman in Ekiti State, Mr Ifedayo Iyanuwura lauded INEC for the transparent manner in which the materials were distributed. Some of the materials distributed were Bimodal Voters Accreditation System, BIVAS machines, Ballot papers, Result sheets, Booklets, Forms EC 8A, B, C, D,E, forms EC 4zero G, 4 zero G1 and 2.